<Category category="Monitoring Devices" slug="transformer-temperature-monitoring-devices" title="Transformer Temperature Monitoring Devices | INNO" description="Review transformer temperature monitoring devices and systems for oil temperature, level, pressure and RS485 remote acquisition. Request technical data." heading="Transformer Temperature Monitoring Devices" eyebrow="Remote monitoring system supplier" intro="Use a powered monitoring device when an oil-immersed transformer project requires digital temperature, level or pressure values at a remote terminal." definition="A transformer temperature monitoring device uses powered sensing and electronics to acquire one or more operating variables and transmit them to a compatible display, RTU, PLC or supervisory system. It differs from a self-contained mechanical OTI or WTI." selectionTitle="How to Select a Transformer Temperature Monitoring Device" selectionText="Define the measured variables, sensor arrangement, DC supply, analog or RS485 interface, protocol, scaling and alarm responsibility. Confirm tank mounting, oil compatibility, enclosure protection, receiving terminal and commissioning method." />
